                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/49.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Oil Fields of Mexico Company states that jefe politico of Tuxpam has requested
                    company to subscribe two thousand dollars monthly to support State troops.</p>
                <p>Make formal protest to appropriate authorities against imposition of this forced
                    loan upon American citizens.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
